==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Halibut
<hw>Hal"i*but</hw> <pr>(h⟦ocr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*b⟦ucr⟧t; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>hali</ets> holy + <ets>but</ets>, <ets>butte</ets>,
flounder; akin to D. <ets>bot</ets>, G. <ets>butte</ets>; cf. D.
<ets>heilbot</ets>, G. <ets>heilbutt</ets>. So named as being eaten on
holidays. See <er>Holy</er>, <er>Holiday</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large, northern, marine flatfish (<spn>Hippoglossus
vulgaris</spn>), of the family <fam>Pleuronectidae</fam>. It often grows
very large, weighing more than three hundred pounds. It is an important
food fish.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>holibut</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

